An ore whose main deposit is located in Central Africa and from which the metal tantalum (Ta) is primarily extracted. The name "coltan" is derived from the mineral group columbite-tantalite (coltan = short form). Columbite itself (according to Römpp) is a niobite and tantalite. Coltan is classified as a conflict mineral. Coltan mining in the Congo is mainly concentrated in the Lake Kivu region in the Democratic Republic of the Congo. Internationally known since 2004 due to the battles over exploitation rights between Rwanda and Congo. Coltan is a necessary raw material for the computer and cell phone industry.

Procedure for comparing models based on the maximum likelihood estimation method. Two models are compared in each case: an initial model, which generally contains several model parameters, and a comparison model in which restrictions are imposed on one or more of these parameters. The comparison is always used to check whether the unrestricted model is significantly "better" than the restricted model, i.e. has a better fit. If this is not the case, the restricted model is preferable because it is simpler (and yet not worse in terms of explanatory power). (ILMES - Internet-Lexikon der Methoden der empirischen Sozialforschung)
